<div class="center"><br />Another great video vignette from <a href="http://vimeo.com/user434753">Paul Frederick</a></div>
<p>Well, as it turned out, Dave wasn't able to join us today.  Shucks.  Maybe Gunther will actually hop on a bike next week, so we can get our share of Dave time.</p>
<p>Anyhow, I was solo today, which ended up being good, for I checked my front tire pressure while waiting and realized it was at 45psi&mdash;not so good for road biking.</p>
<p>After getting some air, I headed up Baseline, where I espied Greg <del>composting his knees</del> running toward Chautauqua.  I was sure to point out that it was warm enough to ride in short sleeves, but Greg answered with a flippant guffaw.</p>
<p>Despite the swirling crosswinds, the ride was just peachy.  Not a soul at the summit; only the sound of the wind.  In the distance, I could see some dark clouds enshrouding the Indian Peaks and the infamous brown cloud squatting on the Eastern Plains.</p>
